// After creating this, in VS Code click the environment name in the bottom-right status bar 
// (or Ctrl+Shift+P → "Rest Client: Switch Environment") and pick dev — that's what makes {{baseUrl}} etc. resolve.
// baseurl or usertoken , admin token , categoryid , productid , ticketid , addressid in .vscode/settings.json

### Create Order (logged-in user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "items": [
    { "product": "{{productId}}", "quantity": 2 }
  ],
  "address": "{{addressId}}",
  "idempotencyKey": "test-order-001"
}

### Get My Orders
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/my-orders
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}


http### Update Order Status — Valid Transition (admin only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "processing"
}

### Update Order Status — Invalid Transition (should 400)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "delivered"
}

### Update Order Status — Valid: processing → shipped
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "shipped"
}

### Update Order Status — Valid: shipped → delivered
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "delivered"
}

### Create Order (logged-in user) — creates local order + Razorpay order
# @name createOrder
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "items": [
    { "product": "{{productId}}", "quantity": 1 }
  ],
  "address": "{{addressId}}",
  "idempotencyKey": "test-order-{{$timestamp}}"
}

### Create Order — Insufficient Stock (should 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "items": [
    { "product": "{{productId}}", "quantity": 999999 }
  ],
  "address": "{{addressId}}",
  "idempotencyKey": "test-stock-fail-{{$timestamp}}"
}

### Create Order — Invalid Address (not owned by user, should 404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "items": [
    { "product": "{{productId}}", "quantity": 1 }
  ],
  "address": "000000000000000000000000",
  "idempotencyKey": "test-bad-address-{{$timestamp}}"
}

### Create Order — Duplicate Idempotency Key (should return existing order, 200)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "items": [
    { "product": "{{productId}}", "quantity": 1 }
  ],
  "address": "{{addressId}}",
  "idempotencyKey": "test-order-001"
}

### Get My Orders
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/my-orders
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### Update Order Status — Valid: pending → processing
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "processing"
}

### Update Order Status — Invalid: skip to delivered (should 400)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "delivered"
}

### Update Order Status — Valid: processing → shipped
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "shipped"
}

### Update Order Status — Valid: shipped → delivered
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "delivered"
}